  "text": "Each phase of water is transported separately, but after advection, convective detrainment, and sedimentation the liquid and ice are repartitioned according to (2) with the required heating accounted for. The RK98 parameterization, which governs the conversion from liquid and ice to rain and snow, can subsequently be used with very little modification. We did modify the forms described in RK98 and [CITATION_1] by doubling the thresholds at which cloud ice begins converting to snow and including the heating associated with phase changes in the formulations for rain and snow production.",
